rain_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690533390 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="Identifying trusted training providers: Ensuring genuine accreditations - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Identifying trusted training providers: Ensuring genuine accreditations - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-33_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-34_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-36_">Reputable training companies hold accreditations as one of their most important characteristics. Avoid those that only accredit their own courses. Look for endorsements from organisations that can vouch for the quality of training. Ensure the accreditations they claim are legitimate and not just for show.<br><br>At The Mandatory Training Group, we take pride in our endorsements from <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/blogs/dr-richard-dune/we-are-endorsed-by-skills-for-care" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Skills for Care</span></i></a>, Skills for Health, and <a href="https://cpduk.co.uk/providers/the-mandatory-training-group" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">CPDUK</span></i></a>. It is important to be aware that some training providers may falsely claim to hold endorsements without displaying the correct badge.<br><br>For example, to ensure the authenticity of a  Skills for Care provider, look for the blue and orange Skills for Care logo with a date stamp, which can be found on our website. These accreditations demonstrate our commitment to delivering high-quality training that meets recognised industry standards. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-37_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-39_">Unleashing creativity and expertise: In-house training material design</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Unleashing_creativit